Message.MsgText: DWCT_UriNotFound=DWCT0006E: URI {0} was not found for virtual host {1}.
Message.Explanation: A request for an unknown URI was received.

Message.MsgText: DWCT_NoProtocolFound=DWCT0004E: Server {0} does not have a listening endpoint for protocol {1}.
Message.Explanation: A request was routed to a server, but the server does not have a listening endpoint for the desired protocol.
Message.UserResponse: Either configure a transport with the appropriate protocol for the target server, or change the protocol mapping for the proxy or on demand router (ODR).

Message.MsgText: DWCT_NoTargetAvail=DWCT0001E: No target server is available for application {0}.
Message.Explanation: No target server is available for the application.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure one or more servers are available to run the application.

Message.MsgText: DWCT_UriConflict=DWCT0007E: Routing to Web module {0} of application {1} in cell {2} is disabled because of a URI conflict with Web module {3} of application {4} in cell {5}.
Message.Explanation: The two specified Web modules have the same virtual host and URI. The routing to one of the Web modules is disabled.
Message.UserResponse: Change the context root of one of the Web modules so that no conflict exists.

Message.MsgText: DWCT_NoCloneIdFound=DWCT0003E: Server with clone ID {0} was not found.
Message.Explanation: A client sent a clone ID that is not valid. The server with the clone id might have been deleted, or the client is in error.

Message.MsgText: DWCT_VHostNotFound=DWCT0005E: Virtual host {0} was not found.
Message.Explanation: A request for an unknown virtual host was received.

Message.UserResponse: See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support for possible causes of this problem.
